        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 12 at 2:04PM EDT until July 12 at 2:30PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 204 PM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from Mount Clemens to near Grosse Pointe to Belle Isle,
moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

These severe storms will be near...
St. Clair Shores, Mount Clemens, Grosse Pointe, and Clinton
Township around 210 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these severe thunderstorms include
Northeast Detroit, Harper Woods, Grosse Pointe Shores, Center Line,
Roseville, Hamtramck, Grosse Pointe Woods, Grosse Pointe Park, Grosse
Pointe Farms, and Utica.

People attending Comerica Park  should seek safe shelter immediately!
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with these storms, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
